cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CG, cs.DM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with boundary detection in a mobile ad hoc network. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes an improved version of the Kamada-Kawai algorithm. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper deals with network topology and connectivity. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possible category as the Kamada-Kawai algorithm is a force-directed algorithm used for graph drawing. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also a possible category as the paper proposes novel heuristics and algorithms for energy level reduction.
